Pre-Game Insights: Finland and Republic of Ireland are both trying to get up and running in the UEFA Nations League, as they play their third fixture on Thursday.
Both sides are adrift in League B Group 3, with neither picking up a point in September.
Finland have already lost to Greece and England, leaving them propping up the four-team standings.
The Republic of Ireland lost to England in Dublin and Greece, conceding twice in the second half of the latter game.
Heimir Hallgrimsson stands in danger of becoming the first Ireland manager to lose each of their first three competitive games in charge.
